# .tool-versions template for projects/<name>/<repo>/
#
# Pin per-project runtimes so `brew upgrade` or system drift can't silently
# break an installed project. Compatible with asdf and mise.
#
# Install mise (recommended):
#   brew install mise
#   echo 'eval "$(mise activate zsh)"' >> ~/.zshrc
#
# Then when you cd into a project with .tool-versions, mise uses the pinned
# versions automatically. mise will offer to install missing ones on first cd.
#
# Examples (delete + adjust per project):

# Node-based projects (Quartz-style)
# nodejs 22.11.0

# Bun-based projects (GBrain-style)
# bun 1.3.9

# Python-based projects (Hermes-style — hard pin to 3.11)
# python 3.11.9

# Multi-runtime (Hermes has Python + Node)
# python 3.11.9
# nodejs 22.11.0
